Overall Historical Progression

The topics in your syllabus reflect the evolution of computing over nearly 90 years:

1930s–1950s: Mathematical foundations, logic, computation theory, and early hardware.
1960s–1970s: Operating systems, networking, databases, programming languages, and microprocessors.
1980s–1990s: Personal computing, object-oriented programming, software engineering, the World Wide Web, and multimedia.
2000s: Agile development, virtualization, cloud computing, Git, and large-scale web applications.
2010s: DevOps, containers, Kubernetes, Infrastructure as Code, IoT, and modern AI techniques.
2020s: Generative AI, large language models, AI agents, cloud-native platforms, and advanced observability.




